{"type":"message","id":"7941988c","parentId":"17751c9d","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:29:46.039Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Lead is reporting another issue with the setup script - when running via curl | bash, the \"y/n\" confirmation prompt at the end isn't working. This is a common issue with piped scripts because stdin is already consumed by the curl pipe, so inquirer can't read from the terminal.\n\nLet me look at the install.sh and ahv-setup.js to understand the confirmation flow.\n\nThe issue is:\n1. `curl -fsSL ... | bash` - stdin is consumed by curl\n2. inquirer prompts for y/n confirmation - can't read from terminal\n3. Script hangs or skips\n\nSolutions:\n1. Add `--yes` flag to skip prompts\n\n\n2. Make confirmation automatic when piped\n3. Detect if stdin is a TTY and skip prompts if not\n\nI need to find where the confirmations happen in the setup flow and fix them so the script can run non-interactively when piped.","thinkingSignature":"c3604a4a02095304cb9f94d3ca8bc123fa3e4ab4f1d4c5261141e4f71f987950"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7kvc71vqxjzo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"inquirer\\|prompt\\|confirm\\|skipIntro\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7kvc71vqxjzo_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"skipIntro\\|skip.*intro\\|--yes\\|-y\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/install.sh | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":22,"output":313,"cacheRead":47816,"cacheWrite":468,"totalTokens":48619,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776256177288,"responseId":"062eb7b2e8186c75de096fd816a1d807"}}
