{"type":"message","id":"0c773c43","parentId":"966b6e73","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:39:13.675Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_396zq2wm2t2w_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"367:    const wsDir = path.join(homePath, \"workspaces\", agentId);\n368:    fs.mkdirSync(wsDir, { recursive: true });\n388:    const searchPaths = [\n389:      path.join(process.env.OPENCLAW_HOME || \"\", \"workspaces2\", \"v4-ecosystem-review\", agentId),\n390:      path.join(process.env.HOME || \"\", \".openclaw\", \"workspaces2\", \"v4-ecosystem-review\", agentId),\n391:      path.join(process.env.HOME || \"\", \".openclaw\", \"workspaces\", agentId),\n393:    const coreFiles = [\"SOUL.md\",\"IDENTITY.md\",\"AGENTS.md\",\"USER.md\",\n398:    for (const srcDir of searchPaths) {\n400:        for (const file of coreFiles) {\n403:            fs.copyFileSync(src, path.join(wsDir, file));"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":60,"aggregated":"367:    const wsDir = path.join(homePath, \"workspaces\", agentId);\n368:    fs.mkdirSync(wsDir, { recursive: true });\n388:    const searchPaths = [\n389:      path.join(process.env.OPENCLAW_HOME || \"\", \"workspaces2\", \"v4-ecosystem-review\", agentId),\n390:      path.join(process.env.HOME || \"\", \".openclaw\", \"workspaces2\", \"v4-ecosystem-review\", agentId),\n391:      path.join(process.env.HOME || \"\", \".openclaw\", \"workspaces\", agentId),\n393:    const coreFiles = [\"SOUL.md\",\"IDENTITY.md\",\"AGENTS.md\",\"USER.md\",\n398:    for (const srcDir of searchPaths) {\n400:        for (const file of coreFiles) {\n403:            fs.copyFileSync(src, path.join(wsDir, file));","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776256753633}}
{"type":"message","id":"2cd5d1db","parentId":"0c773c43","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:39:31.926Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue now. The `homePath` is `~/.openclaw` (from `answers.openclawPath`), and `wsDir` is `~/.openclaw/workspaces/{agentId}`. The search paths are:\n\n1. `{OPENCLAW_HOME}/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/{agentId}`\n2. `{HOME}/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/{agentId}`\n3. `{HOME}/.openclaw/workspaces/{agentId}`\n\nAll of these should resolve to `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/senior-backend` (if HOME=/root). \n\nBut the script reported \"No source agent files found\" for every agent, which suggests the search paths aren't resolving to where the files actually are. I'm realizing the workspace files are in `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/senior-backend/`, not in the subdirectories I was checking.\n\nLooking at the search paths in the script, they're checking for `{HOME}/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/senior-backend/`, which matches where the files actually are. But the script is reporting it can't find them—so either the `coreFiles` array is empty, the `copyFileSync` call is failing silently, or there's a different issue with how the paths are being resolved. The backup path confirms the script ran from the right directory, so that's not the problem. I'm wondering if `fs.existsSync()` is somehow reporting false even though the files are there, or if there's a permissions issue preventing the copy. Let me just run the script directly to see what error actually occurs.\n\nActually, I think the real issue is that `homePath` is defaulting to `/root/.openclaw` when `answers.openclawPath` is `$HOME/.openclaw`, and the search paths are checking `$HOME/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/senior-backend` which would resolve to `/root/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/senior-backend` instead of the correct location. So the issue is that when the path contains `$HOME`, it gets substituted with the actual home directory, but the replacement logic only handles `$HOME/` at the start of the string, not `$HOME` in the middle. So if someone enters `$HOME/.openclaw`, only the leading `$HOME/` gets replaced, leaving `.openclaw` behind and creating an invalid path.\n\nThe real problem though is the skills pack decryption failing. I need to figure out what encryption key was actually used to pack the file in the first place, since the hardcoded \"ahv-openclaw-2026\" key might not be correct. Let me test decryption with different possible keys to see which one works.","thinkingSignature":"4ef3bd8ffd68b34f538c02dd841e56eef3feec8186842a854cc4db88fb5b4b48"},{"type":"text","text":"Tìm thấy 2 bug mới:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6sfofm9qo3lq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json, zlib\n\nd = json.load(open('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/skills.pack'))\nentry = d['manifest'][0]\npayload_b64 = d['payloads'][entry['file']]\nbuf = bytes.fromhex(payload_b64)\n\n# Try without decryption first (plain JSON?)\ntry:\n    text = zlib.decompress(buf)\n    print('UNCOMPRESSED (no crypto):', text[:100])\nexcept:\n    pass\n\n# Try XOR decrypt with known keys\nfor key_name, key in [('ahv-openclaw-2026', b'ahv-openclaw-2026'), ('ahv-openclaw', b'ahv-openclaw'), ('test', b'test')]:\n    try:\n        dec = bytes(buf[i] ^ key[i % len(key)] for i in range(len(buf)))\n        try:\n            text = zlib.decompress(dec)\n            print(f'KEY={key_name}: DECRYPTED (first 100 bytes):', text[:100])\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f'KEY={key_name}: decompress fail:', str(e)[:60])\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f'KEY={key_name}: xor fail:', e)\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":332,"output":880,"cacheRead":70738,"cacheWrite":1150,"totalTokens":73100,"cost":{"input":0,"outpu