{"type":"message","id":"211709ee","parentId":"cde3fb94","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:47:12.104Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture. The manifest has 36 entries:- 33 `{agent}/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md` entries (one per agent)\n- 1 `ai-seo/SKILL.md` (flat, no skills subdirectory)\n- 2 `prompt-optimizer/SKILL.md` entries (duplicate)\n\nThe `{agent}/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md` format is double-nested. When unpacked to `~/.openclaw/skills/`, it becomes:- `~/.openclaw/skills/agile-product-owner/skills/agile-product-owner/SKILL.md`\n\nThis should be:\n\n\n- `~/.openclaw/skills/agile-product-owner/SKILL.md`\n\nSo I need to strip the leading `{agent}/` from each entry in the manifest before unpacking. I'll modify the `unpackSkills` function to handle this stripping logic.","thinkingSignature":"3c0108b318ee53856cc05bfc10689e1ad155dbcf36b092bac8c5ce1376568dbd"},{"type":"text","text":"Phát hiện thêm bug: skill pack entries bị double-nested (`{agent}/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md`). Fix trong script để strip prefix đúng:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wu2ep3s2alm1_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js","offset":14,"limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":633,"output":291,"cacheRead":84711,"cacheWrite":656,"totalTokens":86291,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776257225035,"responseId":"062ebbca984102b3fcce84350dc8a4eb"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8f927755","parentId":"211709ee","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:47:12.224Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wu2ep3s2alm1_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// ─── Inline unpack skills (no execSync to avoid timeout) ─────────────────\nfunction unpackSkills(skillsPackPath, destDir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(skillsPackPath)) {\n    console.log(chalk.yellow(`  ⚠️  skills-full.pack not found — skipping skills`));\n    return;\n  }\n  try {\n    const zlib = require(\"zlib\");\n    const SKILL_KEY = \"ahv-openclaw-2026\";\n    const pack = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(skillsPackPath, \"utf8\"));\n    let count = 0;\n    for (const entry of pack.manifest) {\n      const buf = Buffer.from(pack.payloads[entry.file], \"base64\");\n      const kb = Buffer.from(SKILL_KEY, \"utf8\");\n      const dec = Buffer.alloc(buf.length);\n      for (let i = 0; i < buf.length; i++) dec[i] = buf[i] ^ kb[i % kb.length] ^ (i & 0xff);\n      const content = zlib.inflateSync(dec);\n\n      // File path: skills/senior-backend/SKILL.md OR skills/senior-backend/references/...\n      const filePath = path.join(destDir, \"skills\", entry.file);\n      fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(filePath), { recursive: true });\n      fs.writeFileSync(filePath, content);\n\n      // chmod 500 only on SKILL.md, 444 on supporting files\n      if (entry.file.endsWith(\"SKILL.md\")) {\n        fs.chmodSync(filePath, 0o500);\n      } else {\n        fs.chmodSync(filePath, 0o444);\n      }\n      count++;\n    }\n    const skillCount = pack.manifest.filter(e => e.file.endsWith(\"SKILL.md\")).length;\n    const refCount = pack.manifest.length - skillCount;\n    console.log(chalk.dim(`  📦 ${skillCount} skills + ${refCount} refs/scripts/templates unpacked`));\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.log(chalk.yellow(`  ⚠️  Unpack failed: ${err.message}`));\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Banner ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n[513 more lines in file. Use offset=54 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776257232165}}
{"type":"message","id":"6313e6a6","parentId":"8f927755","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:47:20.158Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue. The manifest entries are like `agile-product-owner/skills/agile-product-owner/SKILL.md`. The script uses `path.join(destDir, \"skills\", entry.file)` which would create:\n`~/.openclaw/skills/agile-product-owner/skills/agile-product-owner/SKILL.md`\n\nBut OpenClaw expects:\n`~/.openclaw/skills/agile-product-owner/SKILL.md`\n\nSo the `file` field in the manifest starts with `{agent}/skills/{agent}/` but should just be `skills/{agent}/`. The fix is to strip the leading `{agent}/` from each entry's file path.","thinkingSignature":"68a351e12688d9aa62dde4539712468894dcf5fd268fc36940d4e39196156c31"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_svpf1zm8vmm0_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js","edits":[{"oldText":"      // File path: skills/senior-backend/SKILL.md OR skills/senior-backend/references/...\n      const filePath = path.join(destDir, \"skills\", entry.file);","newText":"      // Manifest entries: \"{agent}/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md\" — strip leading \"{agent}/\" so\n      // it goes to ~/.openclaw/skills/{agent}/SKILL.md (not double-nested)\n      const agentPrefix = entry.file.split(\"/\")[0] + \"/\";\n      const relativePath = entry.file.startsWith(agentPrefix)\n        ? entry.file.slice(agentPrefix.length)\n        : entry.file;\n      const filePath = path.join(destDir, \"skills\", relativePath);"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":613,"output":364,"cacheRead":84928,"cacheWrite":1238,"totalTokens":87143,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776257232230,"responseId":"062ebbd1fe2edda866babc4efed17bca"}}
