{"type":"message","id":"78c5a748","parentId":"c985e653","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:52:57.554Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The install.sh is 114 lines. I can create a GitHub Gist for it. But I don't have a GitHub token available through the GitHub MCP tool. Let me check if there's another way.\n\nActually, the simplest solution is to make the repo public on GitHub. The user can do this manually in the repo settings. Or I can use the GitHub MCP to make it public if I have the right permissions.\n\nWait - do I have GitHub MCP access? Looking at the tools available, I don't see a GitHub MCP tool. The gitlab__ tools are available but not GitHub tools. Let me check.\n\nNo GitHub MCP tool is listed. \n\nSince I can't directly make the repo public or create a Gist without authentication, I'll suggest the user either make the repo public in their GitHub settings or clone it directly and run the install script from there.","thinkingSignature":"24d719cc7b050e206acb310024fafc60782c02ca64eb0796c928c520d73760b2"},{"type":"text","text":"Repo private nên `raw.githubusercontent.com` bị chặn. **2 cách fix:**\n\n**Cách 1 — Make repo public (nhanh nhất):**\n```\nGitHub → repo Settings → Danger Zone → Change visibility → Make public\n```\nXong chạy: `curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/maiychrus25/setup-openclaw/main/install.sh | bash`\n\n**Cách 2 — Clone rồi chạy local:**\n```bash\ngit clone git@github.com:maiychrus25/setup-openclaw.git /tmp/setup-openclaw\ncd /tmp/setup-openclaw && bash install.sh\n```\n\nLead muốn dùng cách nào?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":166,"output":333,"cacheRead":58091,"cacheWrite":621,"totalTokens":59211,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776304367534,"responseId":"062f73f0c30ab2428400dea03aa44f49"}}
