{"type":"message","id":"43a86d49","parentId":"74c31577","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:59:16.588Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's an issue - `bash -s -- --team dev` is not being handled correctly. The `bash -s` takes the script from stdin and passes `--team` as a positional argument, but the install.sh is reading `$1` which is `--team`, not `dev`. Let me check:Actually, looking at the output: `▶ Chay setup cho team: --team` - it's showing `--team` as the team name. This is because `bash -s -- --team dev` passes `--team` and `dev` as positional args to the shell script, but when stdin is a pipe, the positional args might not work as expected.Wait, `bash -s -- --team dev` should work. The `-s` flag means read from stdin, and `--` stops option parsing so `--team dev` are positional args. But then `$1` in the script would be `--team` and `$2` would be `dev`. \n\nThe install script is probably only checking `$1` and ignoring `$2`, so it's treating `--team` as the team name instead of `dev`. When running from a pipe, stdin is already consumed by curl, which creates a piped mode where the script can't read interactive input. The right approach is to set the team and API key through environment variables and let the script detect the piped mode automatically.","thinkingSignature":"0a61332595b14bce852a55376e95924c40b55e07297f795523ebb7f073994003"},{"type":"text","text":"Setup script nhận `--team` sai vị trí qua pipe. Fix:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tfpfvpiywcrq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n 'team=\"${1:-dev}\"\\|TEAM=\\|--team' /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/install.sh | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":456,"output":363,"cacheRead":75230,"cacheWrite":284,"totalTokens":76333,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776304744508,"responseId":"062f756aedfd319ddc250a4cd8c00941"}}
