{"type":"message","id":"165b57f6","parentId":"53eaa096","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:04:04.137Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of the current openclaw.json structure. Let me now:\n\n1. Create a clean baseline config for setup-openclaw based on this structure\n2. Template out credentials (use env var placeholders like `${AHVHOLDING_API_KEY}`)\n3. Keep only 1 bot token (for now, template it)\n4. Define 3 teams: dev, ba, qa with appropriate agent subsets\n5. Fix the installer to not overwrite existing openclaw.json\n\nKey insight from the current config:\n- `env`: AHVHOLDING_API_KEY, GITLAB_TOKEN, GITLAB_URL\n- `models`: ahvholding with baseUrl, apiKey (from env), 2 models\n\n\n- `channels.telegram`: Multiple bots configured (main_bot, agile-product-owner_bot, ai-seo_bot) \n- `mcp.servers`: stitch, gitlab, confluence-qlhv, confluence-dtlx, confluence-all\n\nFor setup-openclaw, I'll create team-specific configs that inherit from a shared base: team-dev.json gets the backend, frontend, and devops agents plus gitlab and confluence MCP servers; team-ba.json gets the product owner and strategy agents; team-qa.json gets the QA agents. I'll template out credentials using placeholders like `${AHVHOLDING_API_KEY}` instead of hardcoding them.\n\nNow I need to generate clean team config files that pull from the current openclaw.json structure, removing the multiple bot tokens so users only provide one, and then update the setup script to check for existing openclaw.json files and skip the overwrite if one exists.","thinkingSignature":"07b6b2bb714df2619847dd850c622cb6da8c8f89fba5988ba15d5a1c2532e9ba"},{"type":"text","text":"Đọc kỹ cấu trúc rồi. Giờ build lại đúng từ baseline:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p55ebjq5d92e_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    c = json.load(f)\n\n# Print agents list\nprint('Agents:', json.dumps(c.get('agents',{}), indent=2)[:2000])\nprint()\n# Print bindings\nprint('Bindings:', json.dumps(c.get('bindings',{}), indent=2)[:1000])\nprint()\n# Print tools\nprint('Tools:', list(c.get('tools',{}).keys()) if isinstance(c.get('tools'),dict) else type(c.get('tools')))\nprint()\n# Print skills\nprint('Skills:', json.dumps(c.get('skills',{}), indent=2)[:500])\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":966,"output":527,"cacheRead":95851,"cacheWrite":614,"totalTokens":97958,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776308627362,"responseId":"062f8494202c5e183068e064f7775a85"}}
