{"type":"message","id":"6268ecba","parentId":"26629bca","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:05:32.633Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to:\n1. Change the write path to `~/.openclaw/openclaw.generated-{team}.json` \n2. Remove the confirmation prompt for write (since it's a new file)\n3. Keep the restart gateway check\n4. Update the summary output to show the generated file pathActually, let me think about this differently. The most user-friendly approach:- If `openclaw.json` exists → generate a new file `openclaw.generated-{team}.json` and tell user to review/merge it- If `openclaw.json` does NOT exist → write `openclaw.json` directly (first-time install)This way:- Existing users are protected (their real config is never overwritten)- New users get the full experience (openclaw.json created)\n\n\nNow I'll update the applyConfig function to handle both cases—generating the output filename based on whether a config already exists, then modify the write step to always save to that generated path without prompting.","thinkingSignature":"a171a666a19957cc044861a20e64277eea5814798512d776acfd8735992f659f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7t9zq5yt6ywe_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '385,410p' /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":221,"output":255,"cacheRead":101257,"cacheWrite":1159,"totalTokens":102892,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776308722768,"responseId":"062f84f426956d3d8d359dab0e40418e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e366ed9f","parentId":"6268ecba","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:05:32.813Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7t9zq5yt6ywe_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"}\n      }\n    }\n    console.log(chalk.green(`  ✅ ${mcpName}`));\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Apply full config ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfunction applyConfig(config, answers, team) {\n  const openclawPath = getOpenclawPath(answers.openclawPath);\n  const homePath = (answers.openclawPath || \"$HOME/.openclaw\").replace(/^\\$HOME/, process.env.HOME || \"\");\n\n  // Ensure directories exist\n  fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(openclawPath), { recursive: true });\n  fs.mkdirSync(path.join(homePath, \"workspaces\"), { recursive: true });\n\n  // Backup\n  if (fs.existsSync(openclawPath)) {\n    fs.copyFileSync(openclawPath, openclawPath + `.backup-${Date.now()}.json`);\n  }\n\n  let finalConfig = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(config));\n\n  // Fix workspaces and agent dirs — replace {{AGENT_HOME}} with actual path\n  if (finalConfig.agents?.defaults?.workspace) {\n    finalConfig.agents.defaults.workspace = finalConfig.agents.defaults.workspace"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":49,"aggregated":"}\n      }\n    }\n    console.log(chalk.green(`  ✅ ${mcpName}`));\n  }\n}\n\n// ─── Apply full config ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfunction applyConfig(config, answers, team) {\n  const openclawPath = getOpenclawPath(answers.openclawPath);\n  const homePath = (answers.openclawPath || \"$HOME/.openclaw\").replace(/^\\$HOME/, process.env.HOME || \"\");\n\n  // Ensure directories exist\n  fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(openclawPath), { recursive: true });\n  fs.mkdirSync(path.join(homePath, \"workspaces\"), { recursive: true });\n\n  // Backup\n  if (fs.existsSync(openclawPath)) {\n    fs.copyFileSync(openclawPath, openclawPath + `.backup-${Date.now()}.json`);\n  }\n\n  let finalConfig = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(config));\n\n  // Fix workspaces and agent dirs — replace {{AGENT_HOME}} with actual path\n  if (finalConfig.agents?.defaults?.workspace) {\n    finalConfig.agents.defaults.workspace = finalConfig.agents.defaults.workspace","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776308732741}}
