{"type":"message","id":"741817c6","parentId":"19af9750","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:09:15.127Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I also need to update `applyCredentials` to handle the new env vars we're using. Currently it only handles `AHVHOLDING_API_KEY`, `GITLAB_TOKEN`, `CONFLUENCE_URL`, `CONFLUENCE_EMAIL`, `CONFLUENCE_TOKEN`, `STITCH_API_KEY`. But our configs now also use `CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL` and `GITLAB_URL`. Let me check and update.Also, I need to update the `buildAnswersFromEnv` to include these new vars.\n\nLet me also check the CURRENT `applyCredentials` and `buildAnswersFromEnv` to see what needs updating.","thinkingSignature":"28b570d328b7c49960cbabc64039d5d89b280688323cc716ab18b77c0207ca64"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s8hsqtw7t8ev_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '294,315p' /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":235,"output":192,"cacheRead":111187,"cacheWrite":2532,"totalTokens":114146,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776308946638,"responseId":"062f85d44bd44ec74e18d26ac1c9fee4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8ba9d41a","parentId":"741817c6","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:09:15.347Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_s8hsqtw7t8ev_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// ─── Apply credentials to config ────────────────────────────────────────\nfunction applyCredentials(config, answers) {\n  // Build replacement map from answers\n  const vars = {\n    AHVHOLDING_API_KEY:  answers.ahvApiKey,\n    GITLAB_TOKEN:        answers.gitlabToken,\n    CONFLUENCE_URL:      answers.confUrl,\n    CONFLUENCE_EMAIL:    answers.confEmail,\n    CONFLUENCE_TOKEN:   answers.confToken,\n    STITCH_API_KEY:      answers.stitchKey,\n  };\n\n  // Replace all {{...}} placeholders recursively\n  const replaced = replacePlaceholders(config, vars);\n\n  // Also update channels.telegram.accounts.main_bot.botToken if telegramBot provided\n  if (answers.telegramBot) {\n    const accounts = replaced.channels?.telegram?.accounts || {};\n    for (const key of Object.keys(accounts)) {\n      if (answers.telegramBot) {\n        accounts[key].botToken = answers.telegramBot;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":78,"aggregated":"// ─── Apply credentials to config ────────────────────────────────────────\nfunction applyCredentials(config, answers) {\n  // Build replacement map from answers\n  const vars = {\n    AHVHOLDING_API_KEY:  answers.ahvApiKey,\n    GITLAB_TOKEN:        answers.gitlabToken,\n    CONFLUENCE_URL:      answers.confUrl,\n    CONFLUENCE_EMAIL:    answers.confEmail,\n    CONFLUENCE_TOKEN:   answers.confToken,\n    STITCH_API_KEY:      answers.stitchKey,\n  };\n\n  // Replace all {{...}} placeholders recursively\n  const replaced = replacePlaceholders(config, vars);\n\n  // Also update channels.telegram.accounts.main_bot.botToken if telegramBot provided\n  if (answers.telegramBot) {\n    const accounts = replaced.channels?.telegram?.accounts || {};\n    for (const key of Object.keys(accounts)) {\n      if (answers.telegramBot) {\n        accounts[key].botToken = answers.telegramBot;","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776308955270}}
