{"type":"message","id":"0270a19a","parentId":"ed217f4f","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:13:07.823Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also, the `teamCfg.agents || []` on line 185 is also a problem because in our new config structure, `teamCfg.agents` is an object. But actually this is used in `buildAnswersFromEnv` indirectly... wait, no. Let me re-read the code.\n\nActually, looking at `loadTemplate`:\n```jsbase.name = teamCfg.name || base.name;\nbase.description = teamCfg.description || base.description;\n```In our generated configs, `teamCfg.name` is at `teamCfg.meta.name` and `teamCfg.description` is at `teamCfg.meta.desc`. So these will be undefined. But that shouldn't cause the \"object is not iterable\" error.\n\n\nThe `openclaw-full.json` has the full agent list, so that part should work fine. I need to check whether `openclaw-full.json` actually exists in the setup repo's configs directory, since the local version might differ from what's on the remote. Looking at the git status output, I can see that `configs/openclaw-full.json` is showing as a new file, which means it hasn't been committed to the repository yet. This is the critical issue—the loadTemplate function depends on this file existing in configs, but it's not there in the remote branch.\n\nLet me verify whether the file was actually pushed or if it got lost somewhere in the process.","thinkingSignature":"d76d5cf44de258588cb054cf10e5d69d2e55b632e313dc5e65a9a9c52ed83b7a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zf3lc85hwd8v_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && node --check bin/ahv-setup.js && echo \"OK\" && git log --oneline origin/feat/full-setup-mcp | head -5 && echo \"---\" && curl -sI \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/maiychrus25/setup-openclaw/feat/full-setup-mcp/configs/openclaw-full.json\" | head -2"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usa