{"type":"message","id":"1ab3ca44","parentId":"f427d278","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:13:34.581Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly. The local HEAD (e051831) has the new configs (configs/openclaw-full.json, updated team-*.json), but the remote `origin/feat/full-setup-mcp` is at 52e1911 which is OLDER and doesn't have these new configs. \n\nThe push output showed \"Everything up-to-date\" which is a lie because the local is AHEAD of remote. Wait, but I ran `git push origin feat/full-setup-mcp:main` and it showed the files being pushed. Let me re-read the push output...\n\nActually, looking at the push output again:\n```To github.com:maiychrus25/setup-openclaw.git\n   b98efa6..e051831  feat/full-setup-mcp -> main\n```\n\nSo it DID push e051831 to main. But the remote `feat/full-setup-mcp` ref is still at 52e1911. The issue is that I pushed `feat/full-setup-mcp -> main` which means I'm updating the `main` branch with the `feat/full-setup-mcp` branch. But I didn't update the `feat/full-setup-mcp` ref on the remote!\n\nThe remote `feat/full-setup-mcp` branch stayed at 52e1911 because I explicitly pushed only to `main`. I need to either push to the `feat/full-setup-mcp` branch on the remote as well, or push without specifying a destination so both refs get updated together.\n\nActually, I realize I can push to both branches in a single command by specifying them both.","thinkingSignature":"b7db3977ed4e401119ca0a2f4d30ccec0541ab6d07a9ed9b336112d063ba6969"},{"type":"text","text":"\nPush lên đúng branch:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vku9idmpslsr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && git push origin feat/full-setup-mcp:feat/full-setup-mcp main:main 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":476,"output":395,"cacheRead":124456,"cacheWrite":833,"totalTokens":126160,"co