{"type":"message","id":"35dbc631","parentId":"e67d6daa","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:13:56.454Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, the main branch was rejected because it's a protected branch (can't force push). This means the previous push to main (b98efa6..23d955a) happened, but now when I try to push to main again with e051831, it fails because the remote main is ahead (has b98efa6..23d955a but not e051831).\n\nWait - but we pushed b98efa6..23d955a to main earlier. And then we pushed e051831 to main which was rejected. But the remote main should be at 23d955a now.\n\nActually, looking at the push history:1. First push: 43d47cf → main (remove ahv-qlhv-fe)\n\n\n2. Second push: 23d955a → main (init config.env/models)3. Third push: b98efa6 → main (add 'all' team) - this succeeded\n4. Then more pushes to feat/full-setup-mcp\n5. Current: trying to push e051831 to main\n\nWait - the current git log shows remote/feat/full-setup-mcp at 52e1911 and main at b98efa6, but local HEAD is at e051831. So I'm trying to push e051831 to main when main is already at b98efa6 on the remote, which is why it's being rejected.\n\nThe push command with the refspec `main:main` should update the remote main branch to match local main, but it's failing because the remote has diverged. I need to check if there are commits on remote main that aren't in local main, or if there's a force push needed. Actually, I realize I might have made multiple pushes to main in parallel - first b98efa6 succeeded, but then there were more pushes (23d955a and earlier commits) that created a divergence.\n\nThe real issue is that I shouldn't be force-pushing to main anyway. Let me just push the feature branch to feat/full-setup-mcp and update main separately or wait for the Lead to merge it in.","thinkingSignature":"3d90ebd16f91c38fb7fc4e26dd5130880869d9de6209140655f933c3e4285688"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r68exlj3a2x6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"c