{"type":"message","id":"25070ef8","parentId":"73840e04","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:15:03.453Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The local clone at `/root/.openclaw-setup/` has the OLD version of `ahv-setup.js` with the buggy `teamAgents = new Set(teamCfg.agents || [])`. The fix I made is only in the workspace, not in the cloned repo. The `git pull` in the install.sh pulls from the remote `feat/full-setup-mcp`, and since the remote now has the updated files, the pull should have updated them.\n\nBut wait - looking at the install.sh, it does `git pull origin feat/full-setup-mcp`. If the remote now has the updated files, the pull should have updated the local clone. But the file shows the old code (lines 185-186 still show the buggy version).\n\n\nThe remote was at 52e1911 before my last push, and the install script must have cloned it then, so it's still pulling the outdated version. Let me trace through the install.sh logic to see where it's actually pulling from and why the clone isn't updating with my changes.","thinkingSignature":"f41c479c9b06fde2cef35ccb32f3fc00f70f89550e6b692295804de26998ab64"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gzk8x16siydf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"pull\\|clone\\|fetch\\|origin\\|INSTALL_DIR\" /root/.openclaw-setup/install.sh | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":366,"output":258,"cacheRead":128103,"cacheWrite":280,"totalTokens":129007,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776309291413,"responseId":"062f872d5000d6bc31277d04f45f8b05"}}
