\n[2m  • Detected piped mode — auto-skipping prompts[0m\n\n╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n║   AHV OpenClaw Setup — Full Stack v2.0         ║\n║   Agents + MCP servers + skills + config        ║\n╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n\n🔍 Kiểm tra prerequisites...\n\n  ✅ Node.js: v22.22.2\n  ✅ npm: 10.9.7\n  ✅ OpenClaw CLI: OK\n\n▶ 👨💻 Team Dev — Backend, Frontend, DevOps, Architecture\n   Agents: 12 | MCP: gitlab, confluence, stitch\n\n\n❌ Loi: object is not iterable (cannot read property Symbol(Symbol.iterator))\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776309442408}}
{"type":"message","id":"0ab69f1f","parentId":"65658b16","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:17:38.285Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still failing. The issue might be in a different part of the code. Let me trace more carefully. The error is \"object is not iterable (cannot read property Symbol(Symbol.iterator))\". This could be happening in the `replacePlaceholders` function or elsewhere.Let me add some debugging. Actually, let me look at the entire flow more carefully:\n\n1. `loadTemplate('dev')` - loads base from `openclaw-full.json` (has 34 agents) and filters by team agents\n2. `buildAnswersFromEnv('dev')` - gets answers from env vars\n3. `applyCredentials(config, answers)` - replaces placeholders4. `applyConfig(config, answers, 'dev')` - writes config to file5. \n\nNow I'm checking the `replacePlaceholders` function more carefully. The error is likely happening when trying to iterate over something that isn't iterable. Looking at the `applyCredentials` function, it's mapping environment variables to credentials like `AHVHOLDING_API_KEY`, `GITLAB_TOKEN`, `CONFLUENCE_URL`, `CONFLUENCE_EMAIL`, `CONFLUENCE_TOKEN`, `STITCH_API_KEY`, and `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`, then passing them to `replacePlaceholders`. The issue might be that one of these values is undefined or the function is trying to iterate over a non-iterable object.\n\nBut wait, the error is actually happening during `loadTemplate`, not `applyCredentials`. Let me trace through what `loadTemplate` does: it loads `openclaw-full.json` which contains the full agent list, then loads the team-specific config from `team-dev.json`, filters the agents by team, filters bindings, and sets workspace and skills paths. I need to check what `team-dev.json` contains to see if there's a type mismatch or missing property somewhere.\n\nLooking at the team config, I see the issue now—the `agents` field is structured as an object with `defaults` and `list`, not a simple array. The `loadTemplate` function is trying to use `teamCfg.agents` as an array with `Set()`, but it's actually an object. I added a fix to handle `Array.isArray(teamCfg.agents)`, but the problem is the install script is still pulling the old code from before my fix was applied. I need to check what's actually in the cloned repository at this point.","thinkingSignature":"bf80fbde0f25f89d29e19362727c1d550d8c100bcc041340e8e5ad33de963cf9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gf2ckvoeu0ox_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"teamAgentIds\\|teamAgents\" /root/.openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":544,"output":544,"cacheRead":132628,"cacheWrite":381,"totalTokens":134097,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776309442472,"responseId":"062f87c4e732cf6901f50eeb99bf40df"}}
