{"type":"message","id":"97620e82","parentId":"c69067b6","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:19:12.126Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead said \"ok\" - they're acknowledging the conversation. Let me check the current state. The install.sh clones from main but the latest code with the teamAgents fix is on feat/full-setup-mcp branch. The install.sh pulls from feat/full-setup-mcp but the clone step uses main. Since the clone step happened first (before we fixed the pull), the local clone is on main branch with the old code.\n\nBut wait - the `git fetch origin feat/full-setup-mcp && git reset --hard origin/feat/full-setup-mcp` SHOULD have updated the files. But it seems like it didn't work.\n\nOh! I see the bug now. \n\nThe clone initially sets up on main with the outdated code, then the fetch-and-reset should pull in the latest changes from the feature branch. But if the reset isn't actually syncing the files, either the fetch didn't complete properly or there's something else going on with how the hard reset is being applied.","thinkingSignature":"4d03618daebd2ad003cc8d03a81f8154ad8a532539f935d01449a316aee0249b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8wr6rhpt6ea9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"fetch\\|reset\\|pull\" /root/.openclaw-setup/install.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":237,"cacheRead":14486,"cacheWrite":25465,"totalTokens":40188,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776309539089,"responseId":"062f8824408b88b33ea8f95023bd8eab"}}
