{"type":"message","id":"baf44f9d","parentId":"26948c21","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:19:33.323Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, `git checkout origin/feat/full-setup-mcp -- .` would checkout from the remote branch directly. But actually what I want is: force reset to the remote branch. Let me use `git fetch` + `git reset --hard origin/feat/full-setup-mcp` combined with `git clean -fd` to remove untracked files. For dirty tracked files, I can use `git stash` or just force checkout.\n\nThe most reliable approach:```bashcd \"$INSTALL_DIR\" && git fetch origin feat/full-setup-mcp && git checkout origin/feat/full-setup-mcp -- . && git reset --hard origin/feat/full-setup-mcp```\n\n\nThe `checkout` command will overwrite any local changes to tracked files, and the reset with clean will handle removing untracked files, so everything should be fresh and in sync with the remote branch.","thinkingSignature":"ce01d8b83a8c65559b104d09342a9fbbd0cfa83eecb378e53854f005d43a0e1c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_emhfbh27495k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && bash -n install.sh && git add install.sh && git diff --cached --stat && git commit -m \"fix(install): force checkout from feat branch to overwrite dirty local files\" && git push origin feat/full-setup-mcp 2>&1 | tail -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":146,"output":276,"cacheRead":39821,"cacheWrite":724,"totalTokens":40967,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776309564123,"responseId":"062f883d9202eb29e515a8bf89a62a2c"}}
