{"type":"message","id":"e54b0cac","parentId":"6174a953","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:20:10.504Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still on `main` branch with the OLD code! The `git checkout origin/feat/full-setup-mcp -- .` didn't update the local files because the local branch is `main`, not `feat/full-setup-mcp`. The checkout command checks out files from the remote branch into the current working tree, but since we're on `main`, the checkout is checking out files from `origin/main`!Wait, `git checkout origin/feat/full-setup-mcp -- .` should check out files FROM the remote branch `origin/feat/full-setup-mcp` into the current working tree, regardless of which branch we're on. Let me test this:","thinkingSignature":"fb7b365a74a3a794d6db1075eef26a53a10565a0a0810fbc0a681b8246505cc4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x4mik8jpkavc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw-setup && git fetch origin feat/full-setup-mcp && git checkout origin/feat/full-setup-mcp -- . && grep -n \"teamAgentIds\" bin/ahv-setup.js | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":253,"output":203,"cacheRead":41468,"cacheWrite":224,"totalTokens":42148,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776309603221,"responseId":"062f8864a8fc8d49b61948c626e036ce"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b7ec8e0","parentId":"e54b0cac","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:20:11.561Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x4mik8jpkavc_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"From https://github.com/maiychrus25/setup-openclaw\n * branch            feat/full-setup-mcp -> FETCH_HEAD\n185:  const teamAgentIds = Array.isArray(teamCfg.agents) ? teamCfg.agents\n187:  const teamAgents = new Set(teamAgentIds);\n191:  const masterAgents = new Set([\"master-orchestrator\",\"prompt-optimizer\", ...teamAgentIds]);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":963,"aggregated":"From https://github.com/maiychrus25/setup-openclaw\n * branch            feat/full-setup-mcp -> FETCH_HEAD\n185:  const teamAgentIds = Array.isArray(teamCfg.agents) ? teamCfg.agents\n187:  const teamAgents = new Set(teamAgentIds);\n191:  const masterAgents = new Set([\"master-orchestrator\",\"prompt-optimizer\", ...teamAgentIds]);","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776309611532}}
{"type":"message","id":"81721d85","parentId":"8b7ec8e0","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:20:30.964Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`git checkout origin/feat/full-setup-mcp -- .` worked! Now the code has `teamAgentIds`. But the install.sh still has the old `git pull origin main --quiet`. The problem is the install.sh has TWO issues:\n\n1. The `git pull origin main --quiet` needs to be changed to use feat/full-setup-mcp\n2. Even after that, `git checkout origin/feat/full-setup-mcp -- .` needs to be added to force overwrite local files\n\nLet me fix install.sh properly. The cleanest approach:\n```bash\ngit fetch origin feat/full-setup-mcp\ngit checkout origin/feat/full-setup-mcp -- .\n\n\n```\n\nOr we can use `git reset --hard origin/feat/full-setup-mcp` which is simpler and works if there are no uncommitted changes. But since the install.sh is fetched fresh each time (it's downloaded via curl), and then the repo is cloned from main, the local repo starts on main branch.\n\nThe real issue is that I'm overcomplicating this. Instead of trying to pull from main and then reset to feat, I should just clone directly from the feat branch or switch branches after cloning. Let me simplify the whole approach.\n\nActually, the cleanest solution is to always clone from the feat branch instead of main. This way the repo starts in the right place and updates correctly without needing branch switches or resets.\n\n```\nREPO=\"https://github.com/maiychrus25/setup-openclaw.git\"\nBRANCH=\"feat/full-setup-mcp\"\nif [ -d \"$INSTALL_DIR/.git\" ]; then\n  info \"Repo da co — pulling latest...\"\n  cd \"$INSTALL_DIR\" && git pull origin \"$BRANCH\"\nelse\n  git clone --quiet --branch \"$BRANCH\" \"$REPO\" \"$INSTALL_DIR\"\nfi\n```\n\nThis way there's no need for fetch or checkout commands—the repo is always in the right state from the start.","thinkingSignature":"eadb5c8a17cebcb936bb864864e6c316fe994dc4759673010d80ed636f9ef677"},{"type":"text","text":"Root cause: repo cloned from `main`, then pull from wrong branch. Fix: clone + pull từ đúng branch `feat/full-setup-mcp`:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c0lkck02h87y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && python3 - << 'PYEOF'\nwith open('install.sh', 'rb') as f:\n    raw = f.read()\n\n# Fix: clone and pull from feat/full-setup-mcp, not main\nold_clone = b'git clone --quiet \"$REPO\" \"$INSTALL_DIR\"'\nnew_clone = b'git clone --quiet --branch feat/full-setup-mcp \"$REPO\" \"$INSTALL_DIR\"'\n\nold_pull = b'''    cd \"$INSTALL_DIR\" && git fetch origin feat/full-setup-mcp && git checkout origin/feat/full-setup-mcp -- . && git reset --hard origin/feat/full-setup-mcp'''\n\nnew_pull = b'''    cd \"$INSTALL_DIR\" && git pull origin feat/full-setup-mcp'''\n\nok = []\nif old_clone in raw:\n    raw = raw.replace(old_clone, new_clone)\n    ok.append('clone')\nelse:\n    ok.append('clone NOT FOUND')\n\nif old_pull in raw:\n    raw = raw.replace(old_pull, new_pull)\n    ok.append('pull')\nelse:\n    ok.append('pull NOT FOUND')\n\nprint('✅' if len(ok)==2 else f'❌ {ok}', ok)\n\nwith open('install.sh', 'wb') as f:\n    f.write(raw)\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":226,"output":741,"cacheRead":41585,"cacheWrite":438,"totalTokens":42990,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776309611564,"responseId":"062f886cceb60163141e4c0ef7c24b6b"}}
