{"type":"message","id":"dc0b60b6","parentId":"4bb4d703","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:21:59.123Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It's cached! `max-age=300` (5 minutes) and `x-cache: HIT`. The file is served from GitHub's CDN cache. Since the cache TTL is 5 minutes, I just need to wait a bit. But there's a better solution: use the specific commit SHA in the clone URL instead of the branch name for the self-update. This ensures we're always using the exact commit we want.\n\nActually, the simplest fix is to make the `git clone` command use `--branch feat/full-setup-mcp`. But since the curl is cached, I need to either:\n1. Wait for cache to expire\n2. Use a different URL (like the API to get the raw content)\n\n\n3. Add a cache-busting query parameter to force the CDN to fetch a fresh version\n\nThe real issue is that the cached version still has the old clone command without the branch flag. Rather than waiting or finding a workaround, I should update the `REPO` variable to include the branch reference directly, so the clone always pulls from the right place.","thinkingSignature":"9ed6898b614d8a2ce8cf73ef473f7889939308f02814a129e0ae571257ee1b92"},{"type":"text","text":"CDN cache hit — file is stale. Wait out cache TTL then test:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qqrpyuqgi5m2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sleep 30 && curl -fsSL \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/maiychrus25/setup-openclaw/feat/full-setup-mcp/install.sh\" | grep -n \"clone\\|branch\" | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":233,"output":300,"cacheRead":45158,"cacheWrite":371,"totalTokens":46062,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776309708091,"responseId":"062f88cd250d85a4f127f5fa796da7a0"}}
