{"type":"message","id":"8ff48162","parentId":"73367780","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:22:20.629Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"While waiting, let me think about a better solution. The real issue is that the CDN caches files by URL. When I push new code to the same branch, the CDN still serves the old cached version for up to 5 minutes.\n\nSolutions:\n1. **Wait for cache to expire** (what I'm doing now)2. **Use commit SHA instead of branch name** — more reliable but requires knowing the SHA ahead of time\n3. **Use a unique URL each time** — e.g., add `?v=<timestamp>` or `?ref=<branch>` to bust cache\n4. **Push to main instead of feat branch** — since the raw URL from `main` would be the targetActually, the cleanest solution for the install.sh is to have it self-update by fetching from the exact commit it was downloaded at. \n\nI'm trying to figure out how to capture the exact commit SHA when the script downloads, but that's tricky since the curl command itself doesn't expose the response metadata. I could use the GitHub API to fetch the file and get the commit SHA from the response headers, but that's adding unnecessary complexity.\n\nThe simplest fix is just to wait for the CDN cache to expire—the file will refresh automatically within 5 minutes.","thinkingSignature":"eb8a0ff7936f68aa3d3784926452554a5853c16e36aedba6e273e1f28609233b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9nxdn6jvihc5_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"rapid-wharf","timeout":60000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":172,"output":303,"cacheRead":45303,"cacheWrite":634,"totalTokens":46412,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776309729295,"responseId":"062f88e202d848eb6ce7841affe5ee5b"}}
