{"type":"message","id":"903f74e9","parentId":"908b07d6","timestamp":"2026-04-17T14:46:19.499Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. Looking at the git rev-list:\n\n```\n2cdc958 WIP on main: 5b86a7c memory: log 2026-04-11...\nfce1866 index on main: 5b86a7c memory: log 2026-04-11...\n5b86a7c memory: log 2026-04-11 dashboard fix...\n```\n\nThese are the remnants of the OLD repo (`my-setup-openclaw`) that got mixed into this DTLX repo when the workspace was converted. These commits exist in the git objects database because they were originally in the `.git` directory when the workspace was the setup-openclaw repo.\n\n\nThe current `origin/develop` is actually at `497c986`, which is a merge commit that brought in the login redesign, but those files aren't in the working tree. The real problem is that the workspace was converted from the setup-openclaw repo to the DTLX repo while preserving the old git objects, leaving behind orphaned commits like `5b86a7c` that point back to the previous repository state.\n\nWhen `origin/develop` was checked out at `497c986`, it only restored the files from that specific commit, not the entire history—so even though `55f75b7` is in the git history as an ancestor, its actual file changes were never written to the working tree because they were superseded by the merge commit that came after it. I'm realizing the merge commit `eb3da1b` should include the login redesign changes, but the working tree doesn't reflect them—which suggests the files might have been overwritten or reverted after the merge. Let me check if `src/pages/auths/Login.jsx` is actually different between the merge commit and where we are now. I see the issue now—the workspace was converted from a different repository, and when the DTLX repo was set up, its commit history got mixed in. The old `5b86a7c` commit from the previous repo was somehow preserved, and now commits like `55f75b7` that should be part of the