{"type":"message","id":"ac825cb9","parentId":"a25b4815","timestamp":"2026-04-17T14:57:41.930Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The migration creates seed data including users. But the MongoDB is empty. The migration is called in `app.ts` with `MigrationSample.migrationSample()`. The issue is that `CREATE_SAMPLE_DB=true` is set in `.env`, so the migration should run and create the seed data.\n\nBut the database is completely empty. This means either:\n1. The migration ran but didn't find the admin credentials or roles\n2. The migration failed silently\n3. The MongoDB was reset after the migration ran\n\nLet me try to manually run the migration to seed the database. But first, let me check if the migration itself might have issues. Actually, let me just restart the backend and see if the migration runs and creates data.\n \nI'm wondering if the migration is being called too early during startup before the MongoDB connection is fully established. Looking at the migration code, it appears to create built-in roles first, then a system admin account. The fact that the database shows no collections suggests the migration might be failing silently or not running at all, so I should try manually triggering it.","thinkingSignature":"57bd0205d7f5b63a2a01bd201fa06b8d87a90df83234b78e78f5b1f19fa5ab6c"},{"type":"text","text":"\nDB `dtlx` trống — migration chưa seed data. Khởi động lại BE để trigger migration:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oxqprokgd00k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pkill -f \"node.*server.js\" 2>/dev/null; sleep 2; \\\n  cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend && \\\n  node dist/server.js > /tmp/dtlx-be.log 2>&1 &\n  sleep 8; tail -20 /tmp/dtlx-be.log","yieldMs":15000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":758,"output":368,"cacheRead":114396,"cacheWrite":259,"totalTokens":115781,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"ca