{"type":"message","id":"28188aee","parentId":"76b2d381","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:08:11.739Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. The `handleLogin` in Login.jsx reads `res?.roles` but the backend login response structure might be different. Let me check what the login API returns:\n\n```javascript\nconst res = await dispatch(login(values)).unwrap();\nconst roles = res?.roles || [];\n```\n\nBut the backend returns `{ status: \"success\", data: { doc, roles, accessToken, refreshToken } }`. So `res` is the full response, and `res.roles` might not exist. Let me check what the auth.api.js returns.","thinkingSignature":"c8f014fce8e8aa56eedd0fa8e6998a8b96dd463fa457a9eb89c9fae57969f72f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ldpf3759x5sa_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend && \\\n  cat src/apis/auth.api.js && \\\n  echo \"---\" && \\\n  sed -n '60,75p' src/pages/auths/Login.jsx"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":415,"output":198,"cacheRead":121379,"cacheWrite":408,"totalTokens":122400,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776438485522,"responseId":"06317fd79aba9536165a3703aaaf6a24"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c1b6e84d","parentId":"28188aee","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:08:11.920Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ldpf3759x5sa_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import API from \"../configs/axiosInterceptor\";\n\nexport const loginApi = async (data) => {\n  if (data.username && data.password) {\n    const url = \"/auth/signin\";\n    const user = await API.post(url, data);\n\n    if (user.status < 400 && !user.data.error_code && user.data.data) {\n      const data = user.data.data;\n      return data;\n    }\n  }\n  return false;\n};\n\n// loginByTokenApi removed as per backend refactor\n\n// export const forgotPassword = async (email) => {\n//     if (email == '') {\n//         return false;\n//     }\n//     const url = '/api-v1/user/forgot-password';\n//     const user = await axios.post(url, {\n//         email: email,\n//     });\n\n//     if (user.status < 400) {\n//         return true;\n//     }\n// };\n\n// export const getUserDetail = async () => {\n//     try {\n//         const url = '/api-v1/user/detail';\n\n//         const user = await API.get(url);\n\n//         if (user.status < 400 && user.data.data) {\n//             const data = user.data.data;\n//             return data;\n//         }\n//     } catch (err) {\n//         throwMessageError(err);\n//         return false;\n//     }\n// };\n\nexport const signUpApi = async (item) => {\n  const { name, email, password } = item;\n  if (name == \"\" || email == \"\" || password == \"\") {\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  const url = \"/users\";\n\n  const user = await API.post(url, item);\n\n  if (user.status < 400 && user.data.data) {\n    const data = user.data.data;\n    return data;\n  }\n};\n\nexport const clearLocal = () => {\n  localStorage.clear();\n};\n\nexport const changePasswordApi = async (payload) => {\n  const res = await API.patch(`/auth/change-password`, payload);\n\n  if (res.status < 400 && !res.data.error_code && res.data) {\n    return res.data;\n  }\n\n  return false;\n};\n---\n  const dispatch = useDispatch();\n  const navigate = useNavigate();\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);\n  const [isHovered, setIsHovered] = useState(false);\n  const passwordRef = React.useRef(null);\n\n  const handleLogin = async (values) => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      const res = await dispatch(login(values)).unwrap();\n      const roles = res?.roles || [];\n      const highestRole = getHighestRole(roles);\n      const home = ROLE_HOME[highestRole] || \"/403\";\n      navigate(home, { replace: true });\n    } catch (error) {\n      showToast(\"error\", \"Lỗi truy cập\", error || \"Tài khoản hoặc mật khẩu không chính xác.\");"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":73,"aggregated":"import API from \"../configs/axiosInterceptor\";\n\nexport const loginApi = async (data) => {\n  if (data.username && data.password) {\n    const url = \"/auth/signin\";\n    const user = await API.post(url, data);\n\n    if (user.status < 400 && !user.data.error_code && user.data.data) {\n      const data = user.data.data;\n      return data;\n    }\n  }\n  return false;\n};\n\n// loginByTokenApi removed as per backend refactor\n\n// export const forgotPassword = async (email) => {\n//     if (email == '') {\n//         return false;\n//     }\n//     const url = '/api-v1/user/forgot-password';\n//     const user = await axios.post(url, {\n//         email: email,\n//     });\n\n//     if (user.status < 400) {\n//         return true;\n//     }\n// };\n\n// export const getUserDetail = async () => {\n//     try {\n//         const url = '/api-v1/user/detail';\n\n//         const user = await API.get(url);\n\n//         if (user.status < 400 && user.data.data) {\n//             const data = user.data.data;\n//             return data;\n//         }\n//     } catch (err) {\n//         throwMessageError(err);\n//         return false;\n//     }\n// };\n\nexport const signUpApi = async (item) => {\n  const { name, email, password } = item;\n  if (name == \"\" || email == \"\" || password == \"\") {\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  const url = \"/users\";\n\n  const user = await API.post(url, item);\n\n  if (user.status < 400 && user.data.data) {\n    const data = user.data.data;\n    return data;\n  }\n};\n\nexport const clearLocal = () => {\n  localStorage.clear();\n};\n\nexport const changePasswordApi = async (payload) => {\n  const res = await API.patch(`/auth/change-password`, payload);\n\n  if (res.status < 400 && !res.data.error_code && res.data) {\n    return res.data;\n  }\n\n  return false;\n};\n---\n  const dispatch = useDispatch();\n  const navigate = useNavigate();\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);\n  const [isHovered, setIsHovered] = useState(false);\n  const passwordRef = React.useRef(null);\n\n  const handleLogin = async (values) => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      const res = await dispatch(login(values)).unwrap();\n      const roles = res?.roles || [];\n      const highestRole = getHighestRole(roles);\n      const home = ROLE_HOME[highestRole] || \"/403\";\n      navigate(home, { replace: true });\n    } catch (error) {\n      showToast(\"error\", \"Lỗi truy cập\", error || \"Tài khoản hoặc mật khẩu không chính xác.\");","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776438491869}}
{"type":"message","id":"504a00fa","parentId":"c1b6e84d","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:08:20.715Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the bug! The `loginApi` returns `data` which is `user.data.data` — which is `{ doc, roles, accessToken, refreshToken }`. So the `res` in `handleLogin` is `{ doc, roles, accessToken, refreshToken }`.\n\nBut `roles` is a top-level key in the response, so `res?.roles` should work. But wait, let me check more carefully...\n\nThe backend returns:\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"doc\": {...},\n    \"roles\": [\"admin\"],\n    \"accessToken\": \"...\",\n    \"refreshToken\": \"...\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe `loginApi` extracts `user.data.data` which is `{ doc, roles, accessToken, refreshToken }`. So `res.roles` should be `[\"admin\"]`.\n\nThen `getHighestRole([\"admin\"])` should return `\"admin\"`.\nThen `ROLE_HOME[\"admin\"]` should return `\"/dashboard\"`.\n\nSo it should redirect to `/dashboard`. But it's going to `/403` instead. This means `getHighestRole` is returning `null` or something wrong.\n\nWait — maybe the issue is that the Login.jsx file was updated with the NEW redesign (`55f75b7`) which uses `res?.roles || []`. But the OLD Login.jsx (108 lines, currently on disk) might have different code. Let me check the current Login.jsx.\n\nActually, the working tree has 108 lines (old Login). Let me check.","thinkingSignature":"f7a050cee54f555c170d3e85e1e55a6f68c2d554cc22282d84a37b625e9086fc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2crw6w8rnhag_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"wc -l /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend/src/pages/auths/Login.jsx && \\\n  sed -n '66,75p' /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend/src/pages/auths/Login.jsx"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":679,"output":417,"cacheRead":121603,"cacheWrite":735,"totalTokens":123434,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776438491939,"responseId":"06317fddd7c93c6c0de1f8646752b66f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4debec22","parentId":"504a00fa","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:08:21.024Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2crw6w8rnhag_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"387 /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend/src/pages/auths/Login.jsx\n  const handleLogin = async (values) => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      const res = await dispatch(login(values)).unwrap();\n      const roles = res?.roles || [];\n      const highestRole = getHighestRole(roles);\n      const home = ROLE_HOME[highestRole] || \"/403\";\n      navigate(home, { replace: true });\n    } catch (error) {\n      showToast(\"error\", \"Lỗi truy cập\", error || \"Tài khoản hoặc mật khẩu không chính xác.\");"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":146,"aggregated":"387 /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend/src/pages/auths/Login.jsx\n  const handleLogin = async (values) => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      const res = await dispatch(login(values)).unwrap();\n      const roles = res?.roles || [];\n      const highestRole = getHighestRole(roles);\n      const home = ROLE_HOME[highestRole] || \"/403\";\n      navigate(home, { replace: true });\n    } catch (error) {\n      showToast(\"error\", \"Lỗi truy cập\", error || \"Tài khoản hoặc mật khẩu không chính xác.\");","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776438500940}}
{"type":"message","id":"b79bcff7","parentId":"4debec22","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:08:31.972Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Login.jsx has 387 lines and the new code. The redirect to /403 happens when `getHighestRole(roles)` returns `null` or a role not in `ROLE_HOME`. This means `roles` is empty `[]`.\n\nLet me check what the auth.api returns more carefully. The backend signin response:\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"doc\": {...},\n    \"roles\": [\"admin\"],\n    \"accessToken\": \"...\",\n    \"refreshToken\": \"...\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`loginApi` returns `user.data.data` = `{ doc, roles, accessToken, refreshToken }`. So `res` should have `roles = [\"admin\"]`.\n\n\nBut the redux store is persisting the token and roles separately — the `login.fulfilled` handler stores `action.payload` which is just `{ doc, roles, accessToken, refreshToken }`, so `state.token = { doc, roles, accessToken, refreshToken }` and `state.roles` should be `[\"admin\"]`. Yet the login page is still getting an empty roles array, which suggests the API response structure might be different than expected.\n\nThe backend login response has `doc` and `roles` as top-level fields in the data object, but when `loginApi` returns `user.data.data`, it's returning that entire object. So `res?.roles` should work unless the response is wrapped differently — maybe the API is returning the full axios response object instead of just the data property, which would mean `res.data.roles` instead of `res.roles`. I'm seeing the full redirect logic now—it's extracting the roles from the login response, determining the highest role, and navigating to the appropriate home page or falling back to /403. Let me trace through the auth slice to understand how the login action handles the response and what the redux state looks like after a successful login.","thinkingSignature":"4397c7638020b3935ca624e6f454651f0b87c4910c280782ce4e2d3b56dd8aa6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_716iml6ilk4f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend && \\\n  cat src/stores/slices/auth.slice.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":233,"output":457,"cacheRead":122135,"cacheWrite":1237,"totalTokens":124062,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776438501044,"responseId":"06317fe62635ae317d75cdaa02296e19"}}
{"type":"message","id":"abcf7208","parentId":"b79bcff7","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:08:32.263Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_716iml6ilk4f_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { createAsyncThunk, createSlice } from \"@reduxjs/toolkit\";\nimport _ from \"lodash\";\nimport { handleError } from \"../../utils/handleError\";\nimport {\n  changePasswordApi,\n  clearLocal,\n  loginApi,\n} from \"../../apis/auth.api\";\n\nexport const login = createAsyncThunk(\n  \"auth/login\",\n  async (values, { dispatch, rejectWithValue }) => {\n    try {\n      const res = await loginApi(values);\n      if (!res) {\n        return rejectWithValue(\"Có lỗi xảy ra\");\n      }\n\n      dispatch(\n        setLocalToken({\n          accessToken: res?.accessToken,\n          refreshToken: res?.refreshToken,\n        })\n      );\n\n      return res;\n    } catch (err) {\n      const errorMsg = handleError(err);\n      return rejectWithValue(errorMsg);\n    }\n  }\n);\n\nexport const getLocalToken = () => {\n  let token = localStorage.getItem(\"accessToken\");\n  if (!token) {\n    token = sessionStorage.getItem(\"accessToken\");\n  }\n  return token ? JSON.parse(token) : null;\n};\n\nexport const getLocalUser = () => {\n  const user = localStorage.getItem(\"user\");\n  return user ? JSON.parse(user) : null;\n};\n\n// loginByToken removed as per backend refactor (no /auth/me)\n\nexport const changePassword = createAsyncThunk(\n  \"auth/changePassword\",\n  async (payload, { rejectWithValue }) => {\n    try {\n      const res = await changePasswordApi(payload);\n      if (!res) return rejectWithValue(\"Invalid password\");\n      return res;\n    } catch (err) {\n      const errorMsg = handleError(err);\n      return rejectWithValue(errorMsg);\n    }\n  }\n);\n\nconst authSlice = createSlice({\n  name: \"auth\",\n  initialState: {\n    user: null,\n    loading: false,\n    error: null,\n    token: null,\n    authAttempted: false,\n  },\n  reducers: {\n    logout: (state) => {\n      state.user = null;\n      clearLocal();\n    },\n    setLocalToken: (state, action) => {\n      const { accessToken, refreshToken, user } = action.payload;\n      localStorage.setItem(\"accessToken\", JSON.stringify(accessToken));\n      localStorage.setItem(\"refreshToken\", JSON.stringify(refreshToken));\n      if (user) {\n        localStorage.setItem(\"user\", JSON.stringify(user));\n      }\n    },\n\n    loadToken: (state) => {\n      state.token = getLocalToken();\n      state.user = getLocalUser();\n      if (state.user) {\n        state.authAttempted = true;\n      }\n    },\n  },\n  extraReducers: (builder) => {\n    builder\n      .addCase(login.pending, (state) => {\n        state.loading = true;\n        state.error = null;\n      })\n      .addCase(login.fulfilled, (state, action) => {\n        state.loading = false;\n        state.user = action.payload;\n      })\n      .addCase(login.rejected, (state, action) => {\n        state.loading = false;\n        state.error = action.payload;\n      })\n\n      // Replaced by local storage loading in ProtectedRoute/App\n  },\n});\n\nexport const { logout, setLocalToken, loadToken } = authSlice.actions;\nexport default authSlice.reducer;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":65,"aggregated":"import { createAsyncThunk, createSlice } from \"@reduxjs/toolkit\";\nimport _ from \"lodash\";\nimport { handleError } from \"../../utils/handleError\";\nimport {\n  changePasswordApi,\n  clearLocal,\n  loginApi,\n} from \"../../apis/auth.api\";\n\nexport const login = createAsyncThunk(\n  \"auth/login\",\n  async (values, { dispatch, rejectWithValue }) => {\n    try {\n      const res = await loginApi(values);\n      if (!res) {\n        return rejectWithValue(\"Có lỗi xảy ra\");\n      }\n\n      dispatch(\n        setLocalToken({\n          accessToken: res?.accessToken,\n          refreshToken: res?.refreshToken,\n        })\n      );\n\n      return res;\n    } catch (err) {\n      const errorMsg = handleError(err);\n      return rejectWithValue(errorMsg);\n    }\n  }\n);\n\nexport const getLocalToken = () => {\n  let token = localStorage.getItem(\"accessToken\");\n  if (!token) {\n    token = sessionStorage.getItem(\"accessToken\");\n  }\n  return token ? JSON.parse(token) : null;\n};\n\nexport const getLocalUser = () => {\n  const user = localStorage.getItem(\"user\");\n  return user ? JSON.parse(user) : null;\n};\n\n// loginByToken removed as per backend refactor (no /auth/me)\n\nexport const changePassword = createAsyncThunk(\n  \"auth/changePassword\",\n  async (payload, { rejectWithValue }) => {\n    try {\n      const res = await changePasswordApi(payload);\n      if (!res) return rejectWithValue(\"Invalid password\");\n      return res;\n    } catch (err) {\n      const errorMsg = handleError(err);\n      return rejectWithValue(errorMsg);\n    }\n  }\n);\n\nconst authSlice = createSlice({\n  name: \"auth\",\n  initialState: {\n    user: null,\n    loading: false,\n    error: null,\n    token: null,\n    authAttempted: false,\n  },\n  reducers: {\n    logout: (state) => {\n      state.user = null;\n      clearLocal();\n    },\n    setLocalToken: (state, action) => {\n      const { accessToken, refreshToken, user } = action.payload;\n      localStorage.setItem(\"accessToken\", JSON.stringify(accessToken));\n      localStorage.setItem(\"refreshToken\", JSON.stringify(refreshToken));\n      if (user) {\n        localStorage.setItem(\"user\", JSON.stringify(user));\n      }\n    },\n\n    loadToken: (state) => {\n      state.token = getLocalToken();\n      state.user = getLocalUser();\n      if (state.user) {\n        state.authAttempted = true;\n      }\n    },\n  },\n  extraReducers: (builder) => {\n    builder\n      .addCase(login.pending, (state) => {\n        state.loading = true;\n        state.error = null;\n      })\n      .addCase(login.fulfilled, (state, action) => {\n        state.loading = false;\n        state.user = action.payload;\n      })\n      .addCase(login.rejected, (state, action) => {\n        state.loading = false;\n        state.error = action.payload;\n      })\n\n      // Replaced by local storage loading in ProtectedRoute/App\n  },\n});\n\nexport const { logout, setLocalToken, loadToken } = authSlice.actions;\nexport default authSlice.reducer;","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776438512199}}
{"type":"message","id":"82e35e50","parentId":"abcf7208","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:08:39.657Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue! After login:\n1. `loginApi` returns `{ doc, roles, accessToken, refreshToken }`\n2. `login.fulfilled` sets `state.user = action.payload` = `{ doc, roles, accessToken, refreshToken }`\n3. `setLocalToken` saves `accessToken` and `refreshToken` but NOT `user`\n\nSo `localStorage.getItem(\"user\")` is null.\n\nIn `Login.jsx`:\n```jsconst res = await dispatch(login(values)).unwrap();const roles = res?.roles || [];\n```\n\n`res` is `{ doc, roles, accessToken, refreshToken }`. \n\nSo `res?.roles` should be `[\"admin\"]` and `getHighestRole([\"admin\"])` should return `\"admin\"`. But the user is hitting `/403` instead of the dashboard, which means either `getHighestRole` isn't finding the role or the login response structure doesn't match what the code expects. Let me trace through the login flow more carefully to see what's actually being returned.","thinkingSignature":"db4c382a97567ca61b4be98c3caa25d2c3db11c1823e45a009106c30c0e516fe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_96ox8677kvx0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:5555/api/v1/auth/signin \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"username\":\"admin\",\"password\":\"123456\"}' | python3 -m json.tool"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":782,"output":293,"cacheRead":122950,"cacheWrite":1050,"totalTokens":125075,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776438512274,"responseId":"06317ff177e26889f8d61f4f2d18b212"}}
