{"type":"message","id":"1ce66dbb","parentId":"e498d484","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:08:50.271Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The backend returns `{ doc: { role_name: [\"admin\"] }, permissions: [], accessToken, refreshToken }`. But the frontend expects a top-level `roles` field!\n\n`loginApi` returns `user.data.data` which is `{ doc: {...}, permissions: [], accessToken, refreshToken }`. There's NO top-level `roles` field! The roles are inside `doc.role_name`!\n\nSo `res?.roles` returns `undefined`, `roles = []`, `getHighestRole([])` returns `null`, `home = \"/403\"`.\n\nThe fix: In `Login.jsx`, change `res?.roles` to `res?.doc?.role_name`.\n\n\nNow I'm weighing whether to patch the Login.jsx file directly, update the auth API layer to normalize the response, or align the backend with what the frontend expects. The cleanest approach is fixing it at the Login.jsx level since that's where the mismatch is most apparent.\n\nBut I'm also realizing the backend might have a structural issue—the current response nests roles inside `doc.role_name` when it should probably return them at the top level like the original implementation did. Let me check what the original backend auth response should look like to understand the expected contract.\n\nSince the frontend is already deployed and expecting roles at the top level, the quickest solution is to normalize the data in the Login.jsx file by extracting roles from either `res.roles` or falling back to `res.doc.role_name`.","thinkingSignature":"61669f35d053d1d287505ef3d9fb1f081620450d9552b919cbf49ad75bc46801"},{"type":"text","text":"Found the bug! Backend trả `doc.role_name` nhưng Login đọc `res.roles` (undefined). Fix ngay:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vs3yww1widcw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend && \\\n  sed -n '66,75p' src/pages/auths/Login.jsx"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":605,"output":395,"cacheRead":123538,"cacheWrite":1475,"totalTokens":126013,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776438520026,"responseId":"06317ff95ae83931268fbe39adf4c1b5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9e037a5e","parentId":"1ce66dbb","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:08:50.441Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vs3yww1widcw_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const handleLogin = async (values) => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      const res = await dispatch(login(values)).unwrap();\n      const roles = res?.roles || [];\n      const highestRole = getHighestRole(roles);\n      const home = ROLE_HOME[highestRole] || \"/403\";\n      navigate(home, { replace: true });\n    } catch (error) {\n      showToast(\"error\", \"Lỗi truy cập\", error || \"Tài khoản hoặc mật khẩu không chính xác.\");"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":69,"aggregated":"const handleLogin = async (values) => {\n    setLoading(true);\n    try {\n      const res = await dispatch(login(values)).unwrap();\n      const roles = res?.roles || [];\n      const highestRole = getHighestRole(roles);\n      const home = ROLE_HOME[highestRole] || \"/403\";\n      navigate(home, { replace: true });\n    } catch (error) {\n      showToast(\"error\", \"Lỗi truy cập\", error || \"Tài khoản hoặc mật khẩu không chính xác.\");","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776438530392}}
