{"type":"message","id":"3abae2d2","parentId":"e4aa6d9b","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:09:13.809Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see several places that use `user.roles` from the auth state. But the backend returns `doc.role_name` not `roles`. Let me check if `auth.slice.js` already handles this correctly or if we need to normalize in the `login.fulfilled` handler.\n\nIn `auth.slice.js`:\n```js\n.addCase(login.fulfilled, (state, action) => {\n  state.loading = false;\n  state.user = action.payload;  // { doc, permissions, accessToken, refreshToken }\n});\n```\n\n`state.user = { doc: {..., role_name: [\"admin\"]}, permissions: [], accessToken: \"...\", refreshToken: \"...\" }`\n\n\nSo the user's role is nested as `state.user.doc.role_name`, but everywhere else in the codebase is trying to access `state.user.roles` which doesn't exist. I need to flatten this structure in the `login.fulfilled` handler to move `doc.role_name` up to the top level as `roles`, then also pass the full user object to `setLocalToken` so it gets persisted correctly.","thinkingSignature":"07f6d33e03750d144d68e8810a3d5dea941d5e56a9db974100e2efdbb80ef668"},{"type":"text","text":"Nhiều chỗ đọc `user.roles` nhưng backend trả `doc.role_name`. Fix từ gốc:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w8coiyc8bgc5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend && \\\n  python3 - << 'PYEOF'\nwith open('src/stores/slices/auth.slice.js', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\nold = '''      .addCase(login.fulfilled, (state, action) => {\n        state.loading = false;\n        state.user = action.payload;\n      })'''\n\nnew = '''      .addCase(login.fulfilled, (state, action) => {\n        state.loading = false;\n        const payload = action.payload || {};\n        // Normalize: backend returns { doc: { role_name }, ... } but code expects { roles, ... }\n        state.user = {\n          ...payload,\n          roles: payload.roles || (payload.doc && payload.doc.role_name) || [],\n          doc: payload.doc,\n        };\n      })'''\n\nif old in content:\n    content = content.replace(old, new)\n    print('✅ auth.slice fixed')\nelse:\n    print('❌ not found')\n    print(repr(content[content.find('login.fulfilled'):content.find('login.fulfilled')+300]))\n\nwith open('src/stores/slices/auth.slice.js', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(content)\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":444,"output":547,"cacheRead":126086,"cacheWrite":475,"totalTokens":127552,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776438542895,"responseId":"06318010909baaeac6c4e8dc6dc106ed"}}
