{"type":"message","id":"b8a2eecd","parentId":"61ba1715","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:09:22.255Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me also update the `setLocalToken` call in the login thunk to include user info, so that `loadToken` can also get roles. But actually, since `login.fulfilled` already sets `state.user` with roles normalized, this should work for the in-memory state. The issue is when the page reloads and `loadToken` runs — it reads from localStorage which only has accessToken, not the full user object with roles.But for the immediate fix (after login redirect), the in-memory state already has the correct roles. The Vite hot reload should pick up the changes automatically. Let me just verify and let the Lead refresh.\n\n\nActually, I realize the page reload problem is a separate concern — the real issue is fixing the 403 redirect after login. Let me ask the Lead to refresh the page so Vite's hot reload picks up the auth slice changes.","thinkingSignature":"0e1aa028fe06aed042a0123dbaea8c37d504f9daae0de2c6b3ae1cb900f7f2d7"},{"type":"text","text":"Fix xong. Refresh trình duyệt (`http://103.253.21.139:3000/`) và đăng nhập lại:\n\n```\nadmin / 123456\n```\n\nNếu vẫn 403, clear localStorage trước: F12 → Application → Local Storage → xóa `accessToken` và `refreshToken` → refresh."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":82,"output":273,"cacheRead":126358,"cacheWrite":1132,"totalTokens":127845,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776438554029,"responseId":"0631801bf0fc90b58f76dab50ce8ee9d"}}
