{"type":"message","id":"0df72d42","parentId":"4bff0c67","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:28:11.614Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I also need to fix the ProtectedRoute to handle the case where `user` is null (e.g., no token stored). And also ensure that after login, the ProtectedRoute doesn't call loadToken which would wipe the user.\n\nActually, the main issue is that after login, the ProtectedRoute's `useEffect` fires because `authAttempted` is `false` (initial state), and it calls `loadToken()`. But `loadToken()` now sets `authAttempted = true`, and the `useEffect` has a dependency on `authAttempted`, so it might re-run...\n\nWait, no. The useEffect in ProtectedRoute:\n```js\nuseEffect(() => {\n    if (!authAttempted && token) {\n      dispatch(loadToken());\n    }\n  }, [authAttempted, token, dispatch]);\n```\n\nThis only dispatches if `authAttempted === false`. After login, `authAttempted` is still `false` (from initial state). So the useEffect fires and calls `loadToken()`. `loadToken()` sets `state.user = getLocalUser()`. But the user WAS just set by `login.fulfilled`. Since `setLocalToken` now stores the user to localStorage, `getLocalUser()` will return the correct user. So the user is preserved. And `authAttempted = true` so the useEffect won't fire again. This should work! Let me verify the fixes are correct and check for any other places where roles might be accessed incorrectly.","thinkingSignature":"b8ec7ab9cbb236443a834cd8a41738e4fcf21f3ac690329cc167973934ea2bc4"},{"type":"text","text":"Fix tối ưu — lưu user vào localStorage để `loadToken` restore đúng:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vn4rk8dvudqz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend && \\\n  # Also fix login.fulfilled to use doc normalization  \n  python3 - << 'PYEOF'\nwith open('src/stores/slices/auth.slice.js', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\nold = '''      .addCase(login.fulfilled, (state, action) => {\n        state.loading = false;\n        const payload = action.payload || {};\n        // Normalize: backend returns { doc: { role_name }, ... } but code expects { roles, ... }\n        state.user = {\n          ...payload,\n          roles: payload.roles || (payload.doc && payload.doc.role_name) || [],\n          doc: payload.doc,\n        };\n      })'''\n\nnew = '''      .addCase(login.fulfilled, (state, action) => {\n        state.loading = false;\n        const payload = action.payload || {};\n        const doc = payload.doc || {};\n        state.user = {\n          ...payload,\n          ...doc,\n          roles: payload.roles || doc.role_name || [],\n        };\n      })'''\n\nif old in content:\n    content = content.replace(old, new)\n    print('✅ login.fulfilled updated')\nelse:\n    print('❌ login.fulfilled not found')\n\nwith open('src/stores/slices/auth.slice.js', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(content)\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":82,"output":655,"cacheRead":127699,"cacheWrite":1562,"totalTokens":129998,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776439679291,"responseId":"06318481f9838b8fc5f6e5c44022dddf"}}
