{"type":"message","id":"56f1bcaa","parentId":"f470cbd3","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:31:37.438Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me also refresh the page in the browser. But I can't do that remotely. The Lead needs to:1. Clear localStorage (F12 → Application → Local Storage → clear)\n2. Refresh the page\n\nActually, the real issue might be that the login is failing because the API is returning the wrong data. Let me also check: is the login actually succeeding? Let me test the login API endpoint.Actually, let me also check if the issue is with the Redux selector returning stale data. The `ProtectedRoute` now has a normalization:```jsconst rawUser = _.get(state, \"auths.user\", null);const user = rawUser ? {\n  ...rawUser,  roles: rawUser.roles || rawUser.role_name || [],\n} : null;\n```\n\nThis should handle all cases where `user.roles` is undefined — it falls back to `user.role_name` or an empty array. And the defensive check `(user.roles || []).includes(r)` handles null/undefined.\n\nNow I should tell the Lead to clear localStorage and refresh the page to test the login flow.","thinkingSignature":"d1cf4f40944f9025ea568ce87fcf5bfb9aa1fbea3cd51ca6f8a9952547053bfd"},{"type":"text","text":"Dev server restart ✅ Cache cleared. Lead làm 2 bước:\n\n1. **F12 → Application → Local Storage → xóa hết tất cả keys**\n2. **Refresh trang `http://103.253.21.139:3000/`**\n3. **Đăng nhập:** `admin` / `123456`\n\nFix đã thêm:\n- `ProtectedRoute` tự normalize `user.roles` từ `role_name` nếu thiếu\n- Defensive check `(user.roles || []).includes()` tránh crash"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":80,"output":363,"cacheRead":133781,"cacheWrite":246,"totalTokens":134470,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776439887973,"responseId":"06318551073397bd8944206e30a10ed7"}}
